 1097
Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I fully accept responsibility for my actions and the consequences they have brought upon me. 

On the day in question, I was driving with a sense of urgency to pick up my family members from the airport. However, in my haste, I made poor decisions. I was driving at a speed higher than the permitted limit and was distracted by a text message from my cousin. These reckless choices led to my collision with a guardrail. Fortunately, no one else was harmed in the incident.

Upon reflection, I now understand the gravity of my actions and the potential harm they could have caused not only to myself but also to others on the road. I deeply regret my careless and aggressive driving behavior that day.

In terms of my involvement, I acknowledge that my actions played a significant role in the occurrence of the accident. My previous record of three penalty points for speeding further demonstrates my lack of responsibility behind the wheel on that occasion.

However, I would like to bring to the court's attention certain mitigating factors. Firstly, I am a 37-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. This indicates that my involvement in this offense was an isolated incident, rather than reflective of any pattern of reckless behavior.

It is also worth noting that outside of this isolated incident, I actively contribute to society through regular donations to the British Heart Foundation. This demonstrates my commitment to making a positive impact on the lives of others.

I acknowledge that I have made a grave mistake, but I assure the court that I have learned from this experience. I am committed to taking the necessary steps to prevent the reoccurrence of such reckless behavior. I am willing to attend driver education programs and adhere to any conditions the court deems necessary to ensure the safety of myself and others on the road.

In conclusion, I stand here today acknowledging my guilt and expressing deep remorse for my actions. I am committed to learning from this experience and taking the appropriate steps to prevent further harm. I respectfully request the court to consider the mitigating factors presented and to impose a fair and just sentence.

Thank you for your consideration.

Sincerely,

Charlotte Porter

