I stand before you today, humbly pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving, fully aware of the consequences of my actions. I wholeheartedly accept responsibility for my behavior and the resulting consequences.

On the day in question, I was driving with a sense of urgency to pick up my family members from the airport. However, in my haste, I made poor decisions. I was driving at a speed higher than the permitted limit and was distracted by a text message from my cousin. These reckless choices led to my collision with a guardrail, for which I am deeply regretful. 

