Furthermore, I want to bring to the court's attention that I have made regular contributions to the British Heart Foundation. As a 37-year-old individual with an otherwise clean record, these donations reflect my commitment to making positive contributions to society. While I deeply regret my actions on this specific day, it is important to consider the entirety of my character and my contributions outside of this offense.

Moreover, I understand that my actions have put not only myself but also everyone around me on the road at risk. I have reflected on the dangerous nature of my behavior and the potential harm it could have caused. I am committed to learning from this experience and ensuring that such behavior is not repeated in the future.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I reiterate my guilty plea and express profound remorse for my actions. I fully understand the seriousness of my offense and the potential consequences it entails. I believe that my guilty plea, along with my regular contributions to the British Heart Foundation, should be considered as significant factors, showcasing my willingness to take responsibility for my actions and make positive contributions to society. I am committed to personal growth and kindly request the court's consideration in determining an appropriate and fair sentence.

Thank you for your attention,
Charlotte Porter

